## Why VQMACC (Not vd4dots)

K=27 for this RGB conv. vd4dots at K=28 (padded) gives VL=7 at e32/M2 -- 11% utilization at VLEN=1024. VQMACC vectorizing N=26 gives VL=26 at e8/M1 = 20% utilization, and eliminates VREDSUM.

## Bug Fix During Port

The _fast variant's boundary computation assumed `out_tensor_dim == floor((in_dim + 2*pad - ker) / stride) + 1`. The non-fast test uses `out_tensor_dim=19` which is smaller than the computed 21. Fixed by capping `x_int_end` and `y_int_end` at `out_tensor_dim` to prevent OOB writes in the interior loop.

